This paper focuses on measuring the publishing efficiency of cities, which involves analyzing the productivity of scientific disciplines, the location of excellent organizations, and international collaboration patterns. These factors are closely related to several sub-categories in computer science, such as digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), software development (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
